.TH "ata_port_desc" 9 "ata_port_desc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_port_desc \- append port description
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ata_port_desc
.BI "(struct ata_port *ap "  ","
.BI "const char *fmt "  ","
.BI "... "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ap" 12
target ATA port
.IP "fmt" 12
printf format string

Format string according to \fIfmt\fP and append it to port
description.  If port description is not empty, " " is added
in-between.  This function is to be used while initializing
ata_host.  The description is printed on host registration.

LOCKING:
None.
.IP "..." 12
variable arguments
